# PCC governor — required-review ownership (ADR-0008 O2, the "last inch").
#
# These are the trust-root files: the classifier, the commit gate, the receipt writer, the trailer
# emitter/auditor, the shared libs, the stakes manifest, the bypass ledger, CI, and the git hooks.
# A change to any of them should require the owner's explicit review,
# because they decide whether every OTHER change is judged honestly (self-modifying-enforcement — see
# ADR-0008). Judging PRs from trusted origin/main (ADR-0008 code side) shrinks the trusted surface to
# `.github/workflows/ci.yml` + branch-protection settings; THIS file + that required-review toggle are
# the owner-side half that code cannot provide.
#
# TO ACTIVATE (owner, one-time): GitHub -> Settings -> Branches -> the `main` rule -> check
# "Require review from Code Owners". CAVEAT (GPT, 2026-07-15): GitHub will not let you approve your
# OWN pull request, so with a single account this either blocks all governor PRs or needs a second
# trusted reviewer identity. Decide per ADR-0008's honest limits; until then this file documents
# intent and is inert.
#
# Replace @farrissimo below if the owner's GitHub handle differs.

